Package: socscrap
Type: Package
Title: Webscraping for social scientists
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Gabriel Alcaras
Maintainer: Gabriel Alcaras <gabriel.alcaras@ehess.fr>
Description: This package is designed to teach a webscraping class to
    social scientists. It provides a working scraper to extract film data
    from a French website, as well as functions and extensive documentation
    of the webscraping process.
License: GNU GPLv3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    tidyverse,
    lubridate,
    xml2,
    rvest,
    httr,
    purrr,
    glue
Suggests: 
    testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    DiagrammeR,
    thematic,
    viridis,
    ggdendro,
    patchwork,
    svglite
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10)
